Today was shaping up to be just like any other day. That is, until an unfortunate event took place. I awoke that morning with some trepidation, already feeling like something bad was about to happen. Little did I know, it would end with a crash of my car through the garage door.
The situation could have been avoided with simple planning and accuracy. I should have left a few minutes earlier, and carefully switched gears on my car. But instead, I rushed out and let my fate depend on something as unpredictable as the popping of corn. It's never comforting to know that my destiny is in the hands of luck. Today arrived with a crash of my car through the garage door.
